label: Engineer
description: Professional engineers who perform technical services and have professional duties and ethical obligations in their practice
text_references: As members of this profession, engineers are expected to exhibit the highest standards of honesty and integrity
Engineers, in the fulfillment of their professional duties, shall:
Engineers shall hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public

label: Public
description: General public whose safety, health, and welfare must be protected by engineers
text_references: Hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public
Engineers shall avoid conduct that deceives the public
Engineers shall strive to serve the public interest

label: Employer
description: Organizations or individuals who employ engineers and receive their professional services
text_references: Act for each employer or client as faithful agents or trustees
Notify employer or client and appropriate authority if judgment is overruled
Warn employers or clients of project issues

label: Client
description: Individuals or organizations who contract engineers for professional services
text_references: Act for each employer or client as faithful agents or trustees
Do not disclose client/employer information without consent
Warn employers or clients of project issues

label: Sales Engineer
description: Engineers who work in sales roles and may make professional product comparisons
text_references: Sales engineers may make professional product comparisons
